OL,3,CNew domes to allow cricket to be
OL,4,Cplayed year round
OL,6,FTwo "transformative" indoor cricket
OL,7,Fdomes are to be built after the
OL,8,Fgovernment pledged to a #1.5 million
OL,9,Finvestment - allowing the sport to be
OL,10,Fplayed year round.
OL,12,FIt is hoped that the domes will open
OL,13,Fup the sport to women, disabled
OL,14,Fplayers, South Asian communities and
OL,15,Fstate school-educated children, and
OL,16,Fhelp to "break down barriers and make
OL,17,Fcricket the most inclusive team sport".
OL,19,FThe England and Wales Cricket Board
OL,20,F(ECB) will build the facilities in
OL,21,FFarington, near Preston, and in Luton.
